    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-29T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-29T04:00:00-05:00" n="462"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.248/193: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-29T10:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 29, 1939—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>852. Your 313, April 26, 5 p.m. I have not the slightest doubt that the members
                    of the French Government have very much in mind the provisions of the Neutrality
                    Act.</p>
                <p>At the same time in view of the proposed amendment of the Neutrality Act
                    introduced by Senator Pittman it is obvious that the French Government hopes
                    that the Act will be modified either before the outbreak of war or immediately
                    thereafter so as to permit the exportation of aeroplanes and aeroplane motors. I
                    have done nothing to encourage or discourage these hopes nor would I feel
                    warranted in doing so in the absence of specific instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
